tokens.description: Who is the inventor of Bitcoin and who owns the BTC address: 1A1zP1eP5QGefi2DMPTfTL5SLmv7DivfNa? Satoshi Nakamoto! But who is Satoshi Nakamoto? Dorian Nakamoto (see IPFS picture), Craig Steven Wright, Dave Kleiman, Hal Finney, Len Sassaman, Nick Szabo, Phil Zimmermann or is there a group of people behind the pseudonym Satoshi Nakamoto? Craig Wright, on the other hand, is assumed by many to be a fraud. Nakamoto said goodbye to the scene on April 23, 2011 with the following words: I've moved on to other things. It's in good hands with Gavin and everyone. This suggests, or one could infer, that it was not one person who finally realized Bitcoin. The most clues of the true identity as well as correlations are with Hal Finney (Token ID: ab7a1db94776b6a1fdf5837aba60fe6f50f6c85f89ef5aa8e20d8aa5e22dfea2), he shared in March 2013 on the Bitcoin forum BitcoinTalk that he was paralyzed but he planned to continue programming until his death. Hal Finney died in August 2014 from the incurable disease ALS. It remains a mystery who or what Satoshi Nakamoto is. The fact is that all of the people mentioned had/have a direct or indirect connection to Satoshi and Bitcoin. One can only speculate about the reasons why Satoshi Nakamoto decided to keep his identity secret. The most likely reason is rooted in personal security. As someone who has created something potentially very powerful with Bitcoin, you don't just make friends. Phil Zimmermann, for example, the inventor of PGP, an encryption method for e-mail communication, was already allowed to experience this: He became a target of the U.S. government and was accused of criminality solely because of his invention. Bitcoin could one day have a major impact on the monetary system and the economy. Satoshi Nakamoto was also aware of this and probably led him to try everything to remain undetected.

Laszlo Hanyecz (laszlo) made the first documented purchase of a good with bitcoin when he bought two Domino's pizzas from jercos for 10,000 BTC. laszlo had made contributions to Bitcoin's source code in the past.
On May 17, 2010, laszlo posted a request to buy pizza with bitcoin. It was on May 22 that he reported successfully trading 10,000 BTC for two pizzas, with jercos ordering the pizza and receiving the coins. The bitcoins were quoted at $41 at the time of the offer.

Bitcoin Pizza Index: The Pizza Index is the value of the bitcoins spent on the pizzas, were they to be sold rather than spent on pizza. It started at $41 when the transaction actually occurred, and rose significantly since then, topping at $15.5 million in April 2017.

Bitcoin Pizza Day: To commemorate the transaction, May 22 is dubbed Bitcoin Pizza Day. Pizza providers worldwide offer discounts to bitcoin users to commemorate laszlo's purchase.

tokens.description: Haling Erlaand is a Norwegian soccer player from planet Krypton. Rumor has it that his mother raised him not on milk, but on Red Bull. Which would explain why he out sprints even Superman. His teammates say about him that he eats like a bear. His favorite foods include Salzburger Nockerln, Dortmunder Pommes Frites with Currywurst and Steoride straight from Arnold Warzenegger's muscle meat. Between his goals he meditates during the game. And if he ever fails to score 3 goals a game, he simply shoots 4 in the next game. He is undoubtedly one of the best soccer players of his time, but he could just as easily be running hurdles or playing table tennis. Who wants to stop this boy when even Superman can't do it.

tokens.description: Graf Drakula was born in 1724 in Transsexualvania after sunset. Only 301 years later, he died at sunset from a rare blood disease. Being easily irritable, he sought relaxation in the blood bath. This got his circulation going and cleansed his liver. The many and long closures made it harder and harder for him to relax, so he opened a vaccination center in his castle, so he sat right at the source and exchanged cheap mRNA for blood. But the blood was not precious, after all, even the already double-vaccinated came. Whether this was the reason for the rare blood disease is now to be investigated.
tokens.name: Graf Drakula

tokens.description: Pablo Escobar was an entrepreneur and exporter from Medellin (Colombia). He became one of the richest people in the world throughout his life. And he did it by exporting gummy bears and vanilla ice cream. Since precisely these two export hits are considered gateway drugs, a worldwide arrest warrant was issued against him. Until his death, he was the head of the Medellin Cartel. The Medellin Cartel was a non-profit organization that mainly gave away their gummy bears to American children. This also casually earned them the nickname the Gummi Bear Gang. Until the 1980s, there was no one who wanted to do anything about the machinations of the Gummi Bear Gang. That changed in Decembear 1993, when Pablo, the dreaded El Patron, was victimized by violent, diabetic and obese Americans.
tokens.name: Pablo Escobar

tokens.description: The Bitcoin Bull is an enigmatic creature that shows up in the crypto market every few months/years. Whenever the market rises, the Bitcoin Bull shows up. Every three years he then shows himself in full glory. Malicious tongues claim that he is then pumped up like 777 bodybuilders. The bull tempts people to put their money into the market so that the bulls pump even more. This goes on until Elon Musk tweets that Bitcoin is hurting the environment and Tesla stops Bitcoin payments. China bans bitcoin mining and central banks raise interest rates. Then the bull market ends and the bull is beaten for now. Kicked in the ass by the bear, Elon Musk, China and central banks. But even if every bull market ends, the bull will come back. Even if it will take 3 years, 3 months and 3 days. Elon is pumping doge and bitcoin again, Tesla is accepting payments with cryptocurrencies again. China is mining again, as if by magic, and central banks have once again put FIAT currencies in the sand.
tokens.name: Bitcoin Bull
